Libraries

    streamlit (imported as st): A web framework utilized to instantly turn Python scripts into
                                interactive web applications without requiring front-end development skills.

    plotly.express (imported as px): A high-level data visualization module used to generate interactive,
                                     complex graphs and charts with minimal code.

    pandas (imported as pd): A core data manipulation library used to read, analyze, and structure
                              tabular data (like spreadsheets or SQL tables) into usable objects.

Functions and Methods

    st.title("..."): A function that renders the main, top-level heading on the user interface of the web app.

    st.selectbox("...", (...)): A function that creates an interactive dropdown menu on the screen.
                                It takes a prompt and a tuple of options, allowing the user to select a single variable.

    st.subheader(...): A function that renders a secondary heading, slightly smaller than the title,
                       often used to label specific sections of the app.

    pd.read_csv("..."): A function that locates a comma-separated values (CSV) file on the computer's storage,
                        reads its raw text, and converts it into a structured Pandas DataFrame object.

    px.scatter(x=..., y=..., labels=...): A function that constructs a scatter plot visualization.
                                          It plots the provided X and Y data points against each other and maps custom
                                          text labels to the axes.

    st.plotly_chart(figure): A function that takes the completed graph object generated by Plotly and
                             forces Streamlit to render it visually on the web page.

